In this work, process models are not only restricted to value estimation of the outcome but can also provide a variance or dispersion, as was applied in Sect. 1.4.2. Furthermore, the given data can include a variance, such as through multiple measurements. Both cases are addressed by allowing the provided data to not be a single measurements but instead be a closed set of feasible data points. This set will be denoted as the tolerance area of the point \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
